    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="729"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7694</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Princess Cantacuzene of the American Central Committee for
                            Russian Relief</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="30" xml:id="d729fn30">The same on Nov. 20 to the Chairman of the
                        American Red Cross.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madam</hi>: I beg to enclose herewith, for your
                    information, a paraphrase of a telegram received from the American High
                    Commissioner at Constantinople, under date of November 15, concerning the
                    evacuation of refugees from the Crimea.<note n="31" xml:id="d729fn31">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_626">p. 626</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0728" n="628" xml:id="pg_628"/>
                <p>As you are no doubt aware, the State Department has no funds available for use in
                    the alleviation of suffering among these refugees, and I am, therefore, calling
                    the matter to your attention in the hope that your organization may be able to
                    assist in taking care of these unfortunate persons.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State,<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norman H. Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Under Secretary of State</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
